featured_reviews.review_id:
Visited Nov 2021.
What can I really say about this place that hasn't already been mentioned here. Wonderful place, not too many visitors since Khambhat is a bit out of the way. You could easily spend 3 - 4 hours here, especially if you like photography. Best time for photography would be early morning. I was here at noon and some areas were too bright while others were dark. See attached pics. One thing I liked about this place was that it did not have the generic 'restored by the ASI' look (like many masjids in Abad).

featured_reviews.review_id:
Oldest Mosque in Khambhat. It was built in 1325 A.D. in the Sultan Age and Empire of Mohammed Tuglagh...
Beautiful place and peaceful environment...

This Mosque Cover under the ASI (Archeological Survey of India)...

Must visit
